glfw
------------------------------------------
GLFW is a free, Open Source, multi-platform library for OpenGL and OpenGL ES
application development. It provides a simple, platform-independent API for
creating windows and contexts, reading input, handling events, etc.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.32-1
  libGL-devel-10.2.9-1
  libGL1-10.2.9-1
  libglfw-devel-3.0.4-1bl1
  libglfw3-3.0.4-1bl1
  libX11-devel-1.6.2-2
  libX11_6-1.6.2-2
  libXi-devel-1.7.4-1
  libXi6-1.7.4-1
  libXrandr-devel-1.4.2-1
  libXrandr2-1.4.2-1
  libXxf86vm-devel-1.1.3-1bl2
  libXxf86vm1-1.1.3-1bl2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.24.51-6
  cmake-2.8.12.2-3
  cygport-0.17.0-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-1
  gcc-objc-4.9.2-1
  make-4.0-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/glfw/glfw

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/glfw/glfw/archive/3.0.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack glfw-3.0.4-X-src.tar.xz
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
        unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./glfw-3.0.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/glfw-3.0.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/glfw-3.0.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libglfw3-3.0.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libglfw-devel-3.0.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(glfw)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/glfw.README
  /usr/share/doc/glfw/COPYING.txt
  /usr/share/doc/glfw/README.md

(libglfw3)
  /usr/bin/cygglfw-3.dll

(libglfw-devel)
  /usr/include/GLFW/glfw3.h
  /usr/include/GLFW/glfw3native.h
  /usr/lib/cmake/glfw/glfwConfig.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/glfw/glfwConfigVersion.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/glfw/glfwTargets-relwithdebinfo.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/glfw/glfwTargets.cmake
  /usr/lib/libglfw.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/glfw3.pc

